<subSubSection lastPageId="56" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="56" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Very variable trailing or twining perennial herb up to 1 m high, stems angled, vegetative parts always hirsute, thinly to densely pubescent, pilose or tomentose. Leaves petiolate, 2.5-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-6 cm, ovate, apex obtuse or acute, often mucronate, margin entire to undulate, base cordate and cuneate onto the petiole, usually auriculate, auricles rounded to acute, entire or dentate; petioles 0.5-1.5 (-6) cm. Flowers 1-3 (-8) in pedunculate, axillary cymes (often clearly dichasial); peduncles 2-14 cm, very variable from specimen to specimen; bracteoles filiform to linear or linear-oblanceolate, acute, 6-14 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1.5 mm, pedicels 5 -15 mm; outer sepals 7-15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 mm, oblong-elliptic, acute or acuminate, bicoloured, sometimes slightly constricted below triangular, slightly deflexed dark green apical portion, inner sepals scarious-margined 8-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-6 mm, 
<pageBreakToken pageId="56" pageNumber="57" start="start">shorter</pageBreakToken>
but broader; corolla 2.8-3.6 cm, white, cream, or pink, unlobed, midpetaline bands pilose, sometimes darker coloured; filaments glandular below; ovary pilose, style pilose, divided c. 9 mm above base, stigmas 3 mm. Capsule pilose; seeds papillose. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
